field.value:
IKernel.AddComponentInstance<T>(object instance) uses T just to generate "key" parameter for IKernel.AddComponentInstance(string key, Type serviceType, object instance), so useer needs to use the following code to add specific instance for some specific serviceType:

kernel.AddComponentInstance<ServiceType>(typeof(ServiceType), classInstance);

if "classInstance" type is different from (derived from)  ServiceType. If T was used for get ServiceType as well, the following line could have been used instead:

kernel.AddComponentInstance<ServiceType>(classInstance);

And if classType and the serviceType is of the same ServiceType type, the normal

kernel.AddComponentInstance(classInstance);

may be still used.
